    <j.0:uses rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/fd_602/1025"/>
    <j.0:event_legal_uses_concept_type_decision rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/fd_602/1025"/>
    <j.0:comment xml:lang="en">Subject to certain editorial re-drafting, the Commission accepts amendments 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 22 and 24. Amendment 1 and 3 are only partially accepted in the part suggesting the removal of the age element from the criteria to impose a refusal of access order. The banning provision based on the flag of the vessel or the absence of a Voyage data recorder are rejected. Amendment 24 proposing a recital on very high risk flags is not accepted since it is not reflected in the Directive.</j.0:comment>
    <j.0:initiated_by rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/COM"/>
